        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Jewish Foster Home<lb/>
                AND<lb/>
                Orphan Asylum&#44;<lb/>
                S. M. FLEISCHMAN&#44; SUPT.<lb/></p>
            <p>Germantown&#44; Phila.&#44; August 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1887<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr. Henry S. Morais<lb/>
                Editor Jewish Exponent.<lb/>
                My dear sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>If having<lb/> come to my notice that several &#40;3 or 4&#41;<lb/> Jewish children have been placed<lb/> in the Bethesda &#40;Christian&#41; Home<lb/> on Chestnut Hill I deem it my duty<lb/> to call your attention to the fact.<lb/>  Since the Jewish press is to a certain<lb/> extent the conservator of Jewish honor<lb/> and not exactly knowing who would<lb/> be the proper party to notify&#44; I<lb/> thought that in case you could not<lb/> give the matter your own personal<lb/> attention&#44; you would know in<lb/> whose hands to place it.  The<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>information comes through Miss<lb/> Amelia Rosenbaum from the<lb/> father of the children who was at<lb/> the &#34;Home&#34; during my temporary<lb/> absence in Cape May.  His name<lb/> is Philip Leberman&#44; residence<lb/> unknown to me&#44; he has two children<lb/> in our &#34;House&#34;.  The mother is in a<lb/> lunatic asylum in Norristown.<lb/>  Of course you will understand<lb/> that this is a <hi rend="underline">private</hi> communi&#45;<lb/>cation made for the purpose of<lb/> enabling the proper authorities<lb/> to prevent Jewish children being<lb/> educated in christian homes.<lb/>  With kind regards&#45;&#45;yours truly<lb/> S. M. Fleischman.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
